<HEADLINE> Detroit's Greisinger Out For Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Detroit Tigers right-hander Seth Greisinger, who  
has been sidelined since opening day, will have surgery on his 
pitching elbow Tuesday and miss the rest of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Greisinger, 23, has a sprained ligament in his right elbow. He  
will have reconstructive surgery in Birmingham, Ala. 
</P>
<P>
	Greisinger was Detroit's first-round pick in the June 1996  
draft. He was called up to the Tigers last season and went 6-9 with 
a 5.12 ERA in 21 starts. 
  	   	
</P>
