<HEADLINE> New Arena Football Team Picks Name </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- While the city still doesn't have an NFL  
team, it does have the Avengers. 
</P>
<P>
	Casey Wasserman, owner and president of Los Angeles' expansion  
franchise in the Arena Football League, announced the team's name 
at a news conference Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Wasserman said he selected Avengers after a list of possible  
nicknames was compiled. 
</P>
<P>
	``It really stuck out above all,'' he said. ``It was what I was  
looking for, new and unique, and captured all the emotion and 
excitement I thought the team should have.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Knights was the runner-up choice, he said.  
</P>
<P>
	The Avengers' team colors will be bright red, dark blue, dark  
gold and bright gold, with the Avenger logo on their red helmets. 
</P>
<P>
	The team will begin play next April at the Staples Center, now  
under construction. 
</P>
<P>
	Wasserman said he plans to hire a coach and general manager in  
August. The team will be able to sign players Aug. 24, a day after 
the league's championship game. The team will also be stocked by an 
expansion draft scheduled for November. 
  	   	
</P>
