<HEADLINE> 'ER' Star Talks To TV Guide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Another ``ER'' star is unsatisfied with his love  
life. 
</P>
<P>
	Noah Wyle, who plays Dr. John Carter, said he is unhappy about  
the uneven relationship this season between his character and 
medical student Lucy Knight, played by Kellie Martin. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's something about an older guy taking advantage of the  
vulnerability of a student that I thought might be problematic,'' 
Wyle said in the June 19 issue of TV Guide. ``I never really bought 
the romance. It came out of left field.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Eriq La Salle, who plays Dr. Peter Benton, has also questioned  
his character's romantic relationships. 
</P>
<P>
	Wyle says he would rather see Carter date the older Dr. Kerry  
Weaver, played by Laura Innes. 
</P>
<P>
	``Now, I could buy that. I pitched that,'' he said. ``How about  
a little Mrs. Robinson?'' 
  	   	
</P>
