<HEADLINE> Santa Anita Track Under New Owner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Lonny T. Powell, president of Turf  
Paradise in Phoenix, was named president and chief executive 
officer of Santa Anita on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Clifford C. Goodrich will resign as executive vice president and  
general manager effective June 30 as part of a move to consolidate 
racetrack management under new owner Frank Stronach. 
</P>
<P>
	Goodrich has been at Santa Anita since 1980.  
</P>
<P>
	Powell will oversee day-to-day operations beginning in July,  
Santa Anita spokesman Stuart Zanville said. Powell, the son of a 
former jockey, has spent five years at Turf Paradise, which is 
owned by Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Powell also will serve as a vice president of Ventures, a new  
subsidiary of Magna International Inc., which purchased Santa Anita 
last December. Ventures will manage all of Magna's non-automotive 
assets. Besides racetracks, Ventures will be involved in leisure 
real estate development and development of media, sports and 
wagering activities in North America and Europe. 
</P>
<P>
	``I have felt the need for some time to move on to other  
ventures and this seems like the appropriate time for me to make 
that transition,'' Goodrich said in a statement. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
