<HEADLINE> Costner Visits College Alma Mater </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OMAHA, Neb. (AP) -- Kevin Costner, in town over the weekend to  
see his alma mater in the College World Series, invited players to 
a screening of his new baseball film. 
</P>
<P>
	Costner, who rooted for his Cal State Fullerton Titans and the  
Stanford Cardinal on Saturday, also attended the screening of ``For 
The Love of The Game,'' signing autographs for a long line of 
players and fans. 
</P>
<P>
	In the film, Costner plays an aging pitcher who is throwing a  
perfect game against the New York Yankees. The film is set over the 
course of the game, with flashbacks to a love story and other 
scenes. Former Fullerton coach Augie Garrido, a longtime Costner 
pal, plays the Yankees' manager. 
</P>
<P>
	``We thought it was fabulous,'' said current Titan coach George  
Horton. 
</P>
<P>
	He said Costner fans, especially women, will appreciate key  
locker room and shower scenes. 
</P>
<P>
	``If you're a Kevin fan, the word will get out,'' Horton said.  
  	   	
