<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hill, McGraw Win at TNN Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- A duet about overpowering love by Faith  
Hill and her husband Tim McGraw won two early awards Monday at the 
TNN Music City News Country Awards. 
</P>
<P>
	``Just to Hear You Say That You Love Me'' was named best song  
and vocal collaboration. 
</P>
<P>
	``Country music fans are the hippest fans in the world, that's  
for sure,'' Hill said. 
</P>
<P>
	Also, Brooks &AMP; Dunn took home their fourth trophy for best vocal  
duo, and the Dixie Chicks were named best vocal band. 
</P>
<P>
	Awards in a dozen fan-voted categories were handed out at the  
Nashville Arena in a show broadcast live by The Nashville Network. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill was the leading nominee with seven, including best female  
vocalist, best album for ``Faith,'' and best video, single and song 
for ``This Kiss.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The nominees for the top category, Entertainer of the Year, were  
George Strait, Alan Jackson, Shania Twain, Garth Brooks and Neal 
McCoy. McCoy won it last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Joining Hill in the best female vocalist category were Twain,  
Reba McEntire, Martina McBride and Trisha Yearwood. Brooks, Vince 
Gill, Jackson, McGraw and Strait were nominated for best male 
vocalist. 
</P>
<P>
	Fans vote for the TNN Music City News Country Awards through  
ballots, or via telephone and the Internet. The two other major 
annual country music awards shows are voted by industry workers. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
