<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Illinova, Dynegy Agree to $2B Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DECATUR, Ill. (AP) -- Midwestern electric utility Illinova Corp.  
and energy marketer Dynegy Inc. are merging in a $2 billion deal 
they say will create a national leader in the rapidly changing 
energy industry. 
</P>
<P>
	The new firm, to be called Dynegy, will create a full-service  
energy company with $7.5 billion in annual revenue, the companies 
said in a joint statement released today. 
</P>
<P>
	Both boards have unanimously approved the merger plans, which  
must be approved by federal and state regulators and shareholders 
for each company. 
</P>
<P>
	The combined company will be based in Houston, where Dynegy is  
currently based. Illinois Power, an Illinova subsidiary that serves 
about 650,000 electric and natural gas customers in central 
Illinois, will keep its Decatur headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
	Under the agreement, Dynegy shareholders will receive either  
0.69 share in the new company for each Dynegy share or $16.50 in 
cash per Dynegy share. Illinova shareholders will exchange their 
shares on a share-for-share basis. 
</P>
<P>
	Chuck Watson, Dynegy's chairman and chief executive, will keep  
his titles in the new company. Charles Bayless, Illinova's 
chairman, president and chief executive, will be a nonexecutive 
director. 
</P>
<P>
	``This strategic combination creates tremendous opportunities  
for each company much faster than either could have achieved on a 
stand-alone basis,'' Watson said. ``Energy convergence is rapidly 
sweeping across the nation and is a major driver for energy 
industry competition and consolidation.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Illinova announced a tentative deal earlier this year to sell  
its troubled Clinton nuclear power plant to AmerGen Energy Co. for 
$20 million -- about $4 billion less than it cost to build. Until 
its restart last month, the plant had been idle for more than two 
years, siphoning millions of dollars from the struggling company. 
</P>
<P>
	``Dynegy, with its experienced leadership and proven track  
record of risk management, profitability and growth, is the ideal 
strategic partner for Illinova,'' Bayless said. ``I am confident 
that, together, we will be a leader in the rapidly evolving energy 
marketplace of the future.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Dynegy, known as Natural Gas Clearinghouse until a year ago,  
began in 1985 as a wholesale marketer of natural gas. In the past 
few years, it has become a full-scale energy marketer. 
</P>
<P>
	Dynegy's major shareholders -- Chevron Corp.; BG PLC, parent of  
British Gas; and Nova Chemicals -- have agreed to the merger, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	The merger is expected to close by the end of the first quarter  
in 2000. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
