<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-14 13:40:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McEnroe Tops Courier in Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEWPORT, R.I. (AP) -- Don't let the gray hair on John McEnroe's  
head fool you, warned Jim Courier. The 40-year-old McEnroe proved 
he can still play a pretty good game of tennis. 
</P>
<P>
	Courier learned that lesson the hard way Monday, losing in  
straight sets to McEnroe, 7-6 (9-7), 6-3 in the Nike Hall of Fame 
Challenge at the International Tennis Hall of Fame. 
</P>
<P>
	``He doesn't use Grecian Formula, but he never misses a  
volley,'' said a grinning Courier at the conclusion of the 
grass-court exhibition match. 
</P>
<P>
	McEnroe clearly appreciated the compliment. But he said he was  
not sure Courier, 28 years old and ranked 60th in the world, had 
given the match his all. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think he was totally taking it easy on me, but he was  
throwing the old man a bone a little bit,'' said McEnroe, who will 
be inducted into the Hall of Fame July 10. 
</P>
<P>
	Neither player could manage a service break in the first set.  
Trailing 6-5, McEnroe forced the tiebreaker by battling to a win in 
the 12th game. 
</P>
<P>
	After edging Courier in the tiebreaker, McEnroe held serve in  
the second set and broke Courier's serve in the eighth game, 
winning 6-3. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
