<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Red Sox' Gordon Placed on 15-Day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Boston closer Tom Gordon, who set a major league  
record by converting 54 straight regular-season save chances before 
blowing his past two opportunities, was placed on the 15-day 
disabled list Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Gordon's strained right elbow also put him on the DL earlier  
this season, from April 18 to May 10. 
</P>
<P>
	After coming off the DL and converting eight consecutive save  
chances, Gordon blew one June 5 against Atlanta and again Friday 
night against the New York Mets. 
</P>
<P>
	The Red Sox recalled right-hander Jin Ho Cho from Triple-A  
Pawtucket to take Gordon's spot on the roster. Cho, who was 0-3 
with an 8.20 ERA last year for Boston, was 7-1 with a 3.41 ERA this 
season at Pawtucket. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
