<HEADLINE> Dollar Gains in European Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was up against most other major  
currencies in European trading Monday. Gold was mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0436, down from $1.0487 Friday.  
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Friday:  
</P>
<P>
	--120.28 Japanese yen, up from 118.12.  
</P>
<P>
	--1.5268 Swiss francs, up from 1.5234.  
</P>
<P>
	--1.4585 Canadian dollars, up from1.4580.  
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6118, up from $1.6095.  
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth: 
</P>
<P>
	--1.8741 German marks, up from 1.8650  
</P>
<P>
	--6.2855 French francs, up from 6.2550  
</P>
<P>
	--2.1116 Dutch guilders, up from 2.1014.  
</P>
<P>
	--1,855.38 Italian lire, up from 1,846.35.  
</P>
