<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market, 
and American Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
                             	 *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
	Wal-Mart up 1/8 at 43 1/8,  
</P>
<P>
	The Bentonville, Ark.-based retailer is buying Asda Group PLC,  
one of Britain's leading supermarket chains, for about $10.7 
billion. Wal-Mart's first move into British retailing follows 
acquisitions that put the largest U.S. retailer into eight 
countries outside the United States. 

</P>
