<HEADLINE> Radke Leaves Game After Getting Hit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Minnesota pitcher Brad Radke had to leave Monday  
night's game against Boston because of a bruised left knee after 
getting hit by John Valentin's line drive. 
</P>
<P>
	Radke, who cruised through the first four innings, gave up a run  
in the fifth before Valentin's hard shot hit him on the leg. He 
recovered to throw out Valentin. 
</P>
<P>
	After sitting on the mound in pain for a few minutes, he was  
helped off the field. Mike Lincoln replaced Radke to start the 
sixth. 
</P>
<P>
	Radke gave up one run and six hits in his five innings.  
  	   	
