<HEADLINE> Clinton To Hit Fund-Raising Trail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton will travel to a half-dozen  
states by the end of July in a schedule heavy with political fund 
raising, the White House said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The schedule includes a two-day Democratic Party retreat in  
Aspen, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton's travel plans include:  
</P>
<P>
	-- June 28: A Democratic National Committee lunch in Connecticut  
(location to be announced), followed by a Democratic congressional 
fund-raising dinner in New York City. 
</P>
<P>
	-- June 30: A DNC dinner in Chicago .  
</P>
<P>
	-- July 13: A speech at the Communications Workers of America  
convention in Miami. 
</P>
<P>
	-- July 23: A DNC dinner in Cincinnati with travel onward to  
Aspen. 
</P>
<P>
	-- July 24-25: The Democratic retreat in Aspen.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
