<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Devil Rays Recall Trammell </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Devil Rays recalled  
outfielder Bubba Trammell from Triple-A Durham and outrighted 
outfielder Terrell Lowery to the minor league club on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Trammell appeared in 47 games with Durham, batting .269 with  
seven homers and 31 RBIs, after spending much of last season with 
the Devil Rays. Lowery, who hit .200 in seven games with Tampa Bay, 
has 72 hours to report to Durham or can elect to become a free 
agent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Devil Rays also announced that reliever Albie Lopez, on the  
disabled list since May 12 with a strained oblique muscle, began a 
rehabilitation assignment with Class A St. Petersburg on Monday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
